about landing gear?
- Learn.

702
00:50:48,200 --> 00:50:50,031
Hillbilly!

703
00:50:50,160 --> 00:50:51,912
Poe.

704
00:50:56,400 --> 00:51:00,109
- Yeah?
- Cyrus wants you to check out
the landing gear.

705
00:51:00,240 --> 00:51:03,152
Then l'll get to see some nice
scenery whippin' by down there.

706
00:51:08,400 --> 00:51:10,197
Trees and stuff.

707
00:51:29,640 --> 00:51:32,552
Goddamn! Ao that's
what happened to Pinball.

708
00:51:32,680 --> 00:51:35,752
Cut him loose. He's slowin'
us down. Dead weight.

709
00:51:35,880 --> 00:51:38,348
Not exactly
a proper burial.

710
00:51:38,480 --> 00:51:40,789
Look at our shit
over there.

711
00:52:00,120 --> 00:52:01,439
Hurry up.

712
00:52:03,920 --> 00:52:05,876
Hillbilly.

713
00:52:06,000 --> 00:52:07,513
Gotcha.

714
00:52:08,760 --> 00:52:11,149
Hurry up, man.

715
00:52:16,720 --> 00:52:18,517
Bye, Pinball.

716
00:52:32,120 --> 00:52:34,998
Oh, boy! You see that?
You see?

717
00:52:35,120 --> 00:52:39,955
Every time we get her waxed,
l get ten feet from the car wash
and then, pow, bird shit.

718
00:52:40,080 --> 00:52:43,277
Well, it's supposed to be
good luck.

719
00:52:45,360 --> 00:52:47,749
- Light's changed.
- Oh, damn.

720
00:53:09,960 --> 00:53:12,076
- You were in the "Q," right?
- Yeah.

721
00:53:12,200 --> 00:53:15,431
And l heard you say
you had 15 years.

722
00:53:16,720 --> 00:53:18,278
That's right.

723
00:53:18,400 --> 00:53:22,313
But then that would put you
on north block. Right?

724
00:53:22,440 --> 00:53:25,238
Yeah.

725
00:53:25,360 --> 00:53:27,794
Yeah. Funny thing.

726
00:53:27,920 --> 00:53:32,550
l was on north block.
l don't know you.

727
00:53:32,680 --> 00:53:35,877
Well, you know what,
uh, pal?

728
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:40,391
What do you think that means?
Nothin'. Not diddly shit.

729
00:53:40,520 --> 00:53:42,750
You see, there were 160 cats
on north block...

730
00:53:42,880 --> 00:53:47,078
and l didn't want to know 159
of them, which included you.

731
00:53:47,200 --> 00:53:49,509
What do you think
about that?

732
00:53:49,640 --> 00:53:51,437
Yeah.

733
00:53:59,200 --> 00:54:01,714
He's a font
of misplaced rage.

734
00:54:01,840 --> 00:54:06,038
Name your cliche. Mother held
him too much, or not enough.

735
00:54:06,160 --> 00:54:08,754
Last picked at kick ball,
late-night sneaky uncle. Whatever.

736
00:54:10,600 --> 00:54:14,195
Now he's so angry, moments of
levity actually cause him pain.

737
00:54:15,320 --> 00:54:16,833
Gives him headaches.

738
00:54:16,960 --> 00:54:19,474
Happiness, for
that gentleman, hurts.

739
00:54:20,560 --> 00:54:22,516
What's wrong with him?

740
00:54:22,640 --> 00:54:25,632
My first thought would be
a lot.

741
00:54:28,360 --> 00:54:29,918
- Hello.
- Hello.

742
00:54:30,040 --> 00:54:32,156
- Hi. l'm, l'm Vince Larkin.
- l'm Tricia Poe.

743
00:54:32,280 --> 00:54:35,670
Nice to meet ya.
This, this must be Casey.

744
00:54:35,800 --> 00:54:38,473
- Hello, Casey.
- Hello, Vince Larkin.
- Nice to meet ya.

745
00:54:39,560 --> 00:54:41,391
Ao how are you doin'?

746
00:54:41,520 --> 00:54:43,750
l'm sorry. That's, uh-- Acratch
that. Dumb question. You--

747
00:54:43,880 --> 00:54:47,156
You wanted to see your husband today,
and then this whole thing happened.

748
00:54:47,280 --> 00:54:50,431
Maybe you could just tell me
exactly what's going on here and--

749
00:54:50,560 --> 00:54:53,358
We're doing everything we can
to get the plane down.

750
00:54:53,480 --> 00:54:56,358
Actually, that's w-why l wanted
to talk to you.

751
00:55:00,520 --> 00:55:02,829
Hey, wait. W-Where'd you get
the rims, man?

752
00:55:02,960 --> 00:55:05,838
My personal shit's
down in the belly.

753
00:55:07,600 --> 00:55:10,068
- Hey, those are my shades.
- They're mine now, sister.

754
00:55:10,200 --> 00:55:12,077
Men!

755
00:55:18,000 --> 00:55:21,675
lt seems that your husband,
Cameron...

756
00:55:21,800 --> 00:55:24,030
had an opportunity to get off
the plane and he didn't do it.

757
00:55:24,160 --> 00:55:26,628
And l was hoping
you could...

758
00:55:26,760 --> 00:55:30,150
maybe help me
figure out why.

759
00:55:30,280 --> 00:55:33,477
That would make two of us.
l don't know.

760
00:55:33,600 --> 00:55:35,511
l mean, it's possible,
it's, it's not uncommon...

761
00:55:35,640 --> 00:55:39,349
that some parolees actually fear
their release date.

762
00:55:39,480 --> 00:55:42,950
A certain degree of institutionalization
sets in. Fear of coming home.

763
00:55:43,080 --> 00:55:45,435
- Fear of living in society.
Any of this make sense?
- No, no.

764
00:55:45,560 --> 00:55:49,155
That's not Cameron. l mean, if you, if
you knew him, if you read his letters...

765
00:55:49,280 --> 00:55:51,919
or if you talked to him
on the phone, you'd know that--

766
00:55:52,040 --> 00:55:56,033
l mean, he's been waitin' for this day
for eight years. He's not gonna--

767
00:55:58,440 --> 00:56:02,797
l mean, look, he's got this little,
this little girl to come home to.

768
00:56:04,600 --> 00:56:06,795
Wouldn't you...

769
00:56:06,920 --> 00:56:08,876
do the same thing?

770
00:56:11,680 --> 00:56:14,638
There'd have to be a pretty strong
reason to keep me on that plane.

771
00:56:14,760 --> 00:56:17,672
Well, knowing Cameron,
l'm sure there is a good reason.

772
00:56:19,760 --> 00:56:24,311
Uh, maybe, if you, if you do
see him or if you talk to him...

773
00:56:24,440 --> 00:56:28,433
maybe you could just tell him
to come home, all right?

774
00:56:28,560 --> 00:56:30,869
Be kinda nice
to have him around.

775
00:56:31,840 --> 00:56:33,671
You got it.

776
00:56:34,760 --> 00:56:36,796
Vince, line one.

777
00:56:39,080 --> 00:56:40,991
This body fell out
of the sky.

778
00:56:41,120 --> 00:56:45,193
Vince Larkin? This is Ted Grasso,
Fresno Police Department.

779
00:56:45,320 --> 00:56:47,515
We got a problem here
with a corpse.

780
00:56:48,960 --> 00:56:50,518
Yeah, it fell out
of the sky.

781
00:56:50,640 --> 00:56:52,471
l don't think
he's an astronaut.

782
00:56:52,600 --> 00:56:55,478
Then what's this got
to do with me?

783
00:56:55,600 --> 00:56:58,160
lt's got your name
written all over it.

784
00:57:03,280 --> 00:57:05,953
Last transponder tag
was in Arizona.

785
00:57:06,080 --> 00:57:08,310
Body falls here,
in Fresno.

786
00:57:08,440 --> 00:57:11,079
Lerner Airfield.
They're turning around.

787
00:57:11,200 --> 00:57:12,713
- They're coming back.
Can you get me Chief--
- Devers.

788
00:57:12,840 --> 00:57:14,671
Please. Thank you.

789
00:57:14,800 --> 00:57:16,950
- Vince?
- Turn around.

790
00:57:17,080 --> 00:57:19,753
Plane's headed to Lerner Airfield. lt's
a small strip about 100 miles from here.

791
00:57:19,880 --> 00:57:23,475
Horseshit! We're tailing the
transponder tag into Arizona.

792
00:57:23,600 --> 00:57:25,795
Listen to me.
A body fell from the sky.

793
00:57:25,920 --> 00:57:28,195
lt had a note on it.

794
00:57:28,320 --> 00:57:31,153
We got 'em vectored
at 12:00 and 30 miles.

795
00:57:31,280 --> 00:57:35,114
- Vince, please, son.
We're right on his tail.
- Just listen to me!

796
00:57:35,240 --> 00:57:37,470
lt was to me!
The note on the body was to me!

797
00:57:37,600 --> 00:57:39,670
- You're chasing the wrong--
- Aw, shut up.

798
00:57:39,800 --> 00:57:41,028
Hello?

799
00:57:42,680 --> 00:57:45,148
Guys, guys! l need a plane
or a chopper now!

800
00:57:45,280 --> 00:57:47,589
Hey, you and me both.
l'm all out.

801
00:57:47,720 --> 00:57:50,280
l've got to get to Lerner Airfield
and l've got about 50 minutes.

802
00:57:50,400 --> 00:57:52,436
Got a fast car,
you can drive it.

803
00:57:56,240 --> 00:57:58,549
Larkin. Vince Larkin.
l'm with the Marshal Aervices.

804
00:57:58,680 --> 00:58:01,148
Aend whatever you got. Aheriff,
state trooper, national guard.

805
00:58:01,280 --> 00:58:03,589
Hold on one minute.

806
00:58:06,280 --> 00:58:08,635
Your men should proceed
with extreme caution.

807
00:58:08,760 --> 00:58:11,069
lt's only a matter of time
before they find the weapons hold.

808
00:58:15,400 --> 00:58:17,914
Larkin. Vince Larkin.
Marshal Aervices.

809
00:58:18,040 --> 00:58:19,837
How do you think
l got the number?

810
00:58:25,440 --> 00:58:28,716
"...appears to the United Atates
Parole Commission that--"

811
00:58:30,280 --> 00:58:32,271
Poe.

812
00:58:32,400 --> 00:58:35,597
Man! Oh, yeah!

813
00:58:37,120 --> 00:58:39,588
Put the bunny
back in the box.

814
00:58:41,600 --> 00:58:44,990
l knew you was a punk.
And l was right.

815
00:58:45,120 --> 00:58:48,112
You been playin' us
all along.

816
00:58:48,240 --> 00:58:50,629
You a free man.

817
00:58:50,760 --> 00:58:54,435
l said, put the bunny...

818
00:58:54,560 --> 00:58:56,915
back in the box.

819
00:59:26,840 --> 00:59:28,910
Die, punk!

820
00:59:36,760 --> 00:59:40,514
Why couldn't you put the bunny
back in the box?

821
00:59:42,880 --> 00:59:46,350
Next, folks, below and to your left,
you'll see the vertical Renoir Cliffs.

822
00:59:49,160 --> 00:59:52,072
We're seconds away from
establishing visual contact.

823
00:59:53,960 --> 00:59:56,599
Holy shit!

824
00:59:56,720 --> 00:59:59,712
Abort! Abort! Abort!

825
00:59:59,840 --> 01:00:04,436
lf that aircraft's carrying
30 prisoners, l'm Elvis Presley.

826
01:00:05,480 --> 01:00:08,199
"Uncle Bob's Acenic Tours."

827
01:00:09,880 --> 01:00:12,952
Ahit!

828
01:00:13,080 --> 01:00:16,789
Three hundred fuckin' miles
to apprehend Ma and Pa fucking Kettle!

829
01:00:16,920 --> 01:00:19,593
We need to get
to Lerner Airfield now!

830
01:00:19,720 --> 01:00:21,790
Get me Vince Larkin.

831
01:00:31,720 --> 01:00:33,995
Two went down,
one came up.

832
01:00:34,120 --> 01:00:37,192
- Wasn't my fault.
- Well, you don't have to tell me.

833
01:00:37,320 --> 01:00:39,914
Most murders are crimes
of necessity rather than desire.

834
01:00:40,040 --> 01:00:44,079
But the great ones,
Dahmer, Gacy, Bundy...

835
01:00:44,200 --> 01:00:46,395
- they did it because it excited them.
- Don't you--

836
01:00:48,320 --> 01:00:50,311
l got nothing in common
with them, with you.

837
01:00:50,440 --> 01:00:53,750
Don't you talk to me!
They were insane.

838
01:00:53,880 --> 01:00:57,190
Now you're talking
semantics.

839
01:00:57,320 --> 01:01:01,029
What if l told you insane
was working 50 hours a week
in some office for 50 years...

840
01:01:01,160 --> 01:01:03,754
at the end of which
they tell you to piss off?

841
01:01:03,880 --> 01:01:06,155
Ending up
in some retirement village...

842
01:01:06,280 --> 01:01:10,478
hoping to die before suffering
the indignity of trying to make
it to the toilet on time.

843
01:01:12,120 --> 01:01:14,236
Wouldn't you consider that
to be insane?

844
01:01:14,360 --> 01:01:19,753
Murdering 30 people,
semantics or not, is insane!

845
01:01:21,400 --> 01:01:23,118
One girl...

846
01:01:23,240 --> 01:01:25,196
l drove through three states
wearing her head as a hat.

847
01:01:25,320 --> 01:01:28,118
lt's my daughter's birthday
today.

848
01:01:28,240 --> 01:01:31,198
Ao please feel free
not to share everything with me.

849
01:02:29,760 --> 01:02:33,548
All right, you damn peckerwoods,
crack the knuckles and hit the crystals.

850
01:02:33,680 --> 01:02:35,875
We're putting this baby
down in a sandbox.

851
01:02:44,560 --> 01:02:47,313
Lerner Tower,
do you copy?

852
01:02:47,440 --> 01:02:50,352
Lerner Tower,
are you there, Phil?

853
01:02:55,080 --> 01:02:56,559
Come on, answer me.

854
01:02:56,680 --> 01:02:59,114
l am landing.

855
01:03:26,280 --> 01:03:28,191
Oh, my God.

856
01:03:28,320 --> 01:03:30,356
Look out!

857
01:04:41,760 --> 01:04:44,433
Lerner Airfield.
l'm so glad to be here.

858
01:04:47,560 --> 01:04:50,154
Thank you
for choosing Con Air.

859
01:04:52,000 --> 01:04:55,959
- Where's the plane, Francisco?
- l don't know. Have patience.

860
01:04:56,080 --> 01:04:59,709
The last guy who told me to have
patience? l burned him down,
and bagged his ashes.

861
01:04:59,840 --> 01:05:01,717
Cyrus, it'll be here.

862
01:05:08,840 --> 01:05:12,355
Hey, you stupid sons of bitches!
Jesus Christ!

863
01:05:18,160 --> 01:05:20,549
l hope he likes sand.

864
01:05:20,680 --> 01:05:23,797
-Muchacho, run and check out the
tower. Have a look-see, yeah?
-All right.

865
01:05:23,920 --> 01:05:27,151
You come with us.

866
01:05:29,920 --> 01:05:32,388
- Let's go. We're gettin' off.
- Boss, l can't.
- Yes, you can. Come on!

867
01:05:32,520 --> 01:05:34,988
- You shouldn't move him.
- l'm getting him off of this plane.

868
01:05:35,120 --> 01:05:38,908
You, you can't move him. He's
too far along. He could go into shock.

869
01:05:39,040 --> 01:05:41,190
Ahe's right, Poe.
Go on, man.

870
01:05:41,320 --> 01:05:43,550
l'm not leaving
without you, or you.

871
01:05:43,680 --> 01:05:46,478
Ah, listen. Here we go.
Ranger boy.

872
01:05:46,600 --> 01:05:49,717
- Right.
- Goddamn it, Poe!

873
01:05:49,840 --> 01:05:52,274
Man, it's time to fight,
fuck or hit the fence.

874
01:05:52,400 --> 01:05:54,709
- l suggest you hit the fence.
- He's right.

875
01:05:54,840 --> 01:05:57,070
Just go.

876
01:05:57,200 --> 01:06:00,397
All right. Here's how it's gonna play.
l'm gonna get you that needle.

877
01:06:00,520 --> 01:06:03,080
Whatever you say, man.
Just do what you gotta do.

878
01:06:03,200 --> 01:06:04,679
Fuck.

879
01:06:04,800 --> 01:06:07,314
All right, you just hang on.
Don't die on me.

880
01:06:08,040 --> 01:06:12,795
Awing low, sweet chariot

881
01:06:12,920 --> 01:06:15,753
Comin' for
to carry me home

882
01:06:15,880 --> 01:06:19,395
Oh, no. What the hell
you think you're doin'?

883
01:06:19,520 --> 01:06:22,114
- lt's time to off the pigs.
- You can't do that.

884
01:06:22,240 --> 01:06:25,073
- Tell me why.
- They're hostages. We need 'em.

885
01:06:25,200 --> 01:06:29,751
- But why the fuck you care?
- Hey, man, come on.

886
01:06:29,880 --> 01:06:33,668
l can't think of a thing
l'd like better...

887
01:06:33,800 --> 01:06:37,998
than to put a bullet in the brain base
of every one of these fuckers!

888
01:06:38,120 --> 01:06:41,874
But the fact of the matter is,
how well you know this Cindino?

889
01:06:42,000 --> 01:06:44,958
l mean, l don't know him that
well myself. Just what l read.

890
01:06:45,080 --> 01:06:48,038
Like how he firebombed
that senator's yacht with two
of his own cousins on board.

891
01:06:48,160 --> 01:06:50,435
Ao what's your point?

892
01:06:50,560 --> 01:06:52,949
Why would he sweat
about killing some hired guns
once they'd served his purpose?

893
01:06:53,080 --> 01:06:56,709
- Now think about that.
- What exactly are we discussing here?

894
01:06:56,840 --> 01:06:59,115
Poe don't want me
to off the pigs.

895
01:06:59,240 --> 01:07:02,789
Well, it's not difficult to surmise how
Nathan here feels about killing guards.

896
01:07:02,920 --> 01:07:05,354
And my own proclivities
are, uh...

897
01:07:05,480 --> 01:07:10,600
well-known and, uh,
